<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>Couldn't you migrate BCC to EC2 and then migrate pieces of it into Elastic Beanstalk (or AppEngine, or Heroku) as you wrap thin service layers around each piece?</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=40></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3466572 href="vote?for=3466572&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%77%35%37%63%72%6c%74%74%64%6f"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3466572></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=kfool">kfool</a> 20 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3466572">link</a></span></div><br>
<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>Which part of the Slicehost to Rackspace migration required the additional time that had not been invested?<p>Also, what do BCC and AR refer to?</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=80></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3466600 href="vote?for=3466600&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%77%35%37%63%72%6c%74%74%64%6f"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3466600></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=ciniglio">ciniglio</a> 20 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3466600">link</a></span></div><br>
